System Requirements

*------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*
| JDK              | 1.4 or above                                                                                                                   |
*------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*
| Memory           | No minimum requirement                                                                                                         |
*------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*
| Disk Space       | The Continuum application is in itself less than 30MB but will use more disk space when it's checking out and building sources |
*------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*
| Operating System | No minimum requirement. Tested on Windows XP, Debian, Fedora Core and Mac OS X                                                 |
*------------------*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------*

 After downloading Continuum see the {{{guides/getting-started/index.html}Getting Started}}
 document for instructions on how to install and start Continuum.

* {Installation} Instructions

 The installation of Continuum consists solely of unpacking the archive in the desired directory. It's that simple!

** Windows 2000/XP

  [[1]] Unzip <<<continuum-1.0-bin.zip>>> to the directory you wish to install Continuum 1.0. These instructions
        assume you chose <<<C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\continuum-1.0>>>

** Unix-based Operating Systems (Linux, Solaris and Mac OS X)

  [[1]] Extract the distribution archive to the directory you wish to install Continuum 1.0. These instructions
        assume you chose <<</usr/local/continuum-1.0>>>. The directory <<<continuum-1.0>>> will be created from
        the archive.
